 The number of individuals that
requested information on how to deal with over-indebtedness rose
64 percent in August from the previous month, the Portuguese
Association for Consumer Protection said today.  A total of 524 people requested information from the
consumer protection group, up from 320 in the previous month,
DECO said in an e-mailed report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
